Business Brief -- Gottschalks Inc.:
   Chain Complies With Probe
   By IRS of Fiscal '85 Taxes
Gottschalks, a regional department store chain based in
Fresno, Calif., said its board was supervising the company's
independent investigation of the matter.
   It said it believed the IRS probe was limited to the
validity of the one deduction, and that it wasn't aware of
"any other irregularities with respect to the financial
records of the company for any years." It continued, "The
results of this investigation by the criminal investigation
division and the degree of its materiality are not presently
known."
   Company officials couldn't be reached to elaborate on the
statement, which was issued after markets closed.